czParametric HandlesParametrické úchopyczGainZesílenífrAbout _JAMinÀ propos de _JAMinfrSelect ColorRégler la couleurczKneeKolenofr%ddb , %dHz - %dHz%ddb , %dHz - %dHzczDisconnectedOdpojenoczJACK Audio Mastering interfaceJACK Audio Mastering interfaceczNameNázevfr<i><b>Spectrum</b></i><i><b>Spectre</b></i>frCouldn't find pixmap file: %sFichier pixmap introuvable: %sczX=input db , Y=output dbX=vstup dB , Y=výstup dBru    The graphic EQ (GEQ) can be used to set gain for specific bands of the audio spectrum.  The center of the band is annotated at the bottom of each fader.  Setting a fader in the GEQ will override the HDEQ in the immediate vicinity of the changed fader and cause that curve to be redrawn.  It will not override the parametric notch settings in the HDEQ.  Clicking the right mouse button on a GEQ control will reset the value to 0.0.
